# Implementation Plan: Offline-First Local AI Mental Health & Nutritional Screening (React Native)

This plan details the steps to set up and build a fully offline-first, local AI-powered mobile application in **React Native (using Expo)** based on the [`react_native_offline_ai_blueprint.md`](file:///c:/Users/kingh/OneDrive/Documents/giziku/react_native_offline_ai_blueprint.md).

The app will run completely offline, with no backend or internet connection required, using local SQLite storage, on-device AI inference simulation (with direct support for ONNX Runtime Mobile), camera captures for physical checks (face, eyes, nails), dynamic questionnaires based on patient age, and local PDF report generation.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Expo Go vs. Development Builds**:
> Native libraries like `@onnxruntime/react-native` and `expo-sqlite` (new version) require custom native code. While we will write the code to support `@onnxruntime/react-native`, we will build a **dynamic fallback simulation** so that the application runs fully and beautifully inside the standard **Expo Go** environment without crashing. To run with the real ONNX execution provider, you will need to run `npx expo prebuild` and compile the app locally.
> We recommend starting with Expo Go and using our simulation engine to test the full E2E flow.

